msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:8
msgid "The project consists of 3 main components:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:10
msgid ""
"The :rust:crate:`sphinx_rustdocgen` crate for extracting and formatting the "
"documentation comments from Rust code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:11
msgid ""
"The :py:mod:`sphinxcontrib_rust` Sphinx extension for parsing the output of "
"the executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:12
msgid "Project documentation and CI for testing and maintaining."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:15
msgid "Rust crate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:17
msgid ""
"The Rust crate has two main modules, :rust:module:`sphinx_rustdocgen::"
"formats` and :rust:module:`sphinx_rustdocgen::directives`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:20
msgid ""
"The ``formats`` module consists of various traits that implement formatting "
"the output as reStructuredText or Markdown. Most code related to formatting "
"the details of a directive lives in this module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:23
msgid ""
"The ``directives`` module and its submodules implement the Rust side of all "
"the :doc:`directives`. The :rust:enum:`~sphinx_rustdocgen::directives::"
"Directive` enum is where new directives should be added first. Each variant "
"of this enum is a newtype for a struct that holds the details of the "
"directive. The structs must implement both :rust:trait:`sphinx_rustdocgen::"
"formats::RstDirective` and :rust:trait:`sphinx_rustdocgen::formats::"
"MdDirective` traits. Take a look at one of the existing directive "
"implementation for an example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:30
msgid "See :doc:`sphinx-rustdocgen` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:33
msgid "Sphinx extension"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:35
msgid ""
"The Sphinx extension is largely dedicated to reading the directive and "
"converting them to content."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:37
msgid ""
"The directives are defined in :py:mod:`sphinxcontrib_rust.directives`. All "
"the directives inherit from the :py:class:`sphinxcontrib_rust.directives."
"RustDirective` class, which handles the options and converts them into the "
"directive's display text."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:41
msgid ""
"The Sphinx domain itself is implemented in :py:mod:`sphinxcontrib_rust."
"domain` module. The domain mostly just manages the directives for "
"referencing and indexing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:44
msgid ""
"The ``__init__.py`` file of the package is the interface for Sphinx to "
"connect with the extension and for the extension to execute the Rust "
"executable to generate the pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:47
msgid "See :doc:`sphinx-extension` for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:50
msgid "Docs and CI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:52
msgid ""
"The CI for the project makes sure that the Rust and Python code are properly "
"formatted and linted as per the :ref:`code-style`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:55
msgid ""
"It will first test the Rust crate and then the Sphinx extension. As part of "
"the test, the project will run on itself. It will also ensure that the "
"Python package can be built and the documentation is generated properly for "
"readthedocs.org and for GitLab pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:60
msgid "Design and execution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:62
msgid "The workflow of the extension is"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:64
msgid ""
"Configure Sphinx to use the extension and add any necessary options. This is "
"also where any monkey patching happens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:66
msgid "Start the Sphinx build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:67
msgid ""
"Once Sphinx has created the builder (``builder-inited`` event), start a "
"subprocess to execute the ``sphinx-rustdocgen`` binary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:69
msgid ""
"The subprocess will traverse the crate, starting with the crate's library "
"and executable files, discovering any modules that were changed since the "
"last build along the way. As long as it has files to process, it will"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:73
msgid ""
"Use syn_ to generate an AST and analyze it to extract the docstrings and "
"identify the visibility of the items in the file. This creates a :rust:"
"struct:`~sphinx_rustdocgen::directives::crate_directive::CrateDirective` "
"struct for the library file, a :rust:struct:`~sphinx_rustdocgen::directives::"
"executable_directive::ExecutableDirective` for each executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:79
msgid ""
"Queue any submodules discovered within the crate and identify their source "
"files. A :rust:struct:`~sphinx_rustdocgen::directives::module_directive::"
"ModuleDirective` struct is generated for the module files discovered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:82
msgid ""
"Write the document for the file to configured output directory, if it was "
"updated, and fetch the next file from the queue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:85
msgid ""
"Once the subprocess completes, Sphinx will run the build process. The :py:"
"mod:`sphinxcontrib_rust` domain will now parse any Rust specific directives "
"and cross-references as they are discovered by Sphinx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../docs/developing.rst:88
msgid "Sphinx build finishes"
msgstr ""
